-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----
EXAMPLE / DOCUMENTATION ONLY — this file is intentionally NOT a valid PEM.
The installer no longer ships a placeholder ``update_pubkey.pem``: shipping
one risked operators leaving the placeholder in place and accepting any
package the verifier did not refuse outright.

To enable signed-update verification on a deployment, generate a real key
pair and drop ONLY the public key (no extension change) at:

    repo/installer/update_pubkey.pem

Generation:

    openssl genpkey -algorithm RSA -pkeyopt rsa_keygen_bits:3072 -out priv.pem
    openssl pkey -in priv.pem -pubout -out installer/update_pubkey.pem

The application's first-run provisioning copies ``installer/update_pubkey.pem``
into the per-user data directory at ``$DATA_DIR/update_pubkey.pem``. If no
public key is present at apply time, the updater rejects every package with
``BizError(SIGNATURE_REQUIRED)``.
-----END PUBLIC KEY-----
